[4:14 am, 04/04/2023] ðŸ‘‘ Mohammed Faisal ðŸ‘‘: List the commands that belongs DDL with example query
DDL (Data Definition Language) commands are used to create, modify, and delete database objects such as tables, indexes, and constraints. Some common DDL commands with example queries are:

CREATE: This command is used to create database objects such as tables, indexes, and views. For example:
sql
Copy code
CREATE TABLE customers (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE,
    age INT
);
ALTER: This command is used to modify the structure of an existing database object. For example:
sql
Copy code
ALTER TABLE customers ADD COLUMN phone VARCHAR(20);
DROP: This command is used to remove a database object such as a table, index, or view. For example:
sql
Copy code
DROP TABLE customers;
TRUNCATE: This command is used to remove all data from a table. For example:
sql
Copy code
TRUNCATE TABLE customers;
RENAME: This command is used to rename a database object. For example:
css
Copy code
ALTER TABLE customers RENAME TO clients;
COMMENT: This command is used to add comments to a database object. For example:
vbnet
Copy code
COMMENT ON TABLE customers IS 'This table contains customer information';
CREATE INDEX: This command is used to create an index on a table to improve query performance. For example:
arduino
Copy code
CREATE INDEX idx_customers_email ON customers (email);
These are some of the common DDL commands used in SQL.
